<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-28T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-28T10:00:00-05:00" n="982" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d982">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/46</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Thurston</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-28T10:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s December 22, 7 p.m. Honduran Government accepts neutral zone
                            and will withdraw all troops south and east of Merendén mountains upon
                            Guatemala withdrawing hers north and east of the Motagua River,
                            reserving right to maintain very small number police. Urge Guatemala to
                            accept at once and troops to be mutually withdrawn by January 1, 1918.
                            Also press for answer to boundary arbitration treaty.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>